<p>Use the <code>.rounded-*</code> utility classes to control the border
radius (rounded corners) of elements. These classes allow consistent
spacing-based rounding or special shapes like pill borders.</p>
<h3 id="doc-syntax">Syntax</h3>
<pre class="css"><code>.rounded-[value]</code></pre>
<p>Where <code>[value]</code> is a number from <code>0</code> to
<code>7</code>, or <code>pill</code>.</p>
<h3 id="doc-available-classes">Available Classes</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr class="header">
<th>Class</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code>rounded-0</code></td>
<td>No border radius (square corners)</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><code>rounded</code></td>
<td>Alias for <code>.rounded-1</code></td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code>rounded-1</code></td>
<td>Border radius of size 1</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><code>rounded-2</code></td>
<td>Border radius of size 2</td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code>rounded-3</code></td>
<td>Border radius of size 3</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><code>rounded-4</code></td>
<td>Border radius of size 4</td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code>rounded-5</code></td>
<td>Border radius of size 5</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><code>rounded-6</code></td>
<td>Border radius of size 6</td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code>rounded-7</code></td>
<td>Border radius of size 7</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><code>rounded-pill</code></td>
<td>Fully rounded (pill-shaped) using <code>50vh</code> radius</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3 id="doc-examples">Examples</h3>
<div
class="rounded-0 w-fit mt-4 card p-4 border dark:border-grey-900 light:border-grey-100">
No rounding
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;rounded-0&quot;&gt;No rounding&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
<div
class="rounded-3 w-fit mt-3 card p-4 border dark:border-grey-900 light:border-grey-100">
Moderate rounding
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;rounded-3&quot;&gt;Moderate rounding&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
<div
class="rounded-pill w-fit mt-3 card p-4 border dark:border-grey-900 light:border-grey-100">
Pill-shaped element
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;rounded-pill&quot;&gt;Pill-shaped element&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
